ST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Henry Empson was born in 1200, in London, England, United Kingdom. He married Mrs. Henry Empson in 1225, in London, Middlesex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1230, in his hometown, at the age of 30."},"et":{"1200–1230":"1200–1230","1205–Female":"1205–Surnud","1224–Male":"1224–Surnud","1205":"1205","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1230":"1230","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","London,Middlesex,England.":"City of London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","London, England, United Kingdom":"London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1200–1230":"1200–1230","1205–Female":"1205–Kuollut","1224–Male":"1224–Kuollut","1205":"1205","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1230":"1230","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","London,Middlesex,England.":"City of London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","London, England, United Kingdom":"London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1200–1230":"1200–1230","1205–Female":"1205–Décédée","1224–Male":"1224–Décédé","1205":"1205","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1230":"1230","London, Middlesex, England":"Londres, Middlesex, Angleterre","London,Middlesex,England.":"City of London, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","London, England, United Kingdom":"Londres, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sir Henry Empson est né en 1200, à Londres, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. 